            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This is ready for review. Some notes:\n- I tried to remove as much stuff from `tests/test_apps` as possible, and use tmpdirs instead. I think all these little files are about as ugly as global state can be.\n- As with Werkzeug, we depend on a development version of tox, because the new version has a much more expressive config format to specify env-dependent requirements.\n- Greenlet is now installed in Travis and the tests are running\n- The memory leak test is still failing, i think we should add more information why we (who?) chose to skip this. I myself have no idea why.\n- I removed `python setup.py audit` as i am not sure anybody uses that. Instead i'd suggest to use pyflakes directly, or better IMO, flake8.\n"
